<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/127037-i-loved-this-book-but-i-have-2-things">I loved this book, but I have 2 things that bothered me a little. I haven&#39;t been to England, so I don&#39;t know, are villages there really as closed to differences as this book implies? And, Major Pettigrew is only 68 yet in some ways he seemed older, in fact, at times I though him an Agatha Christie character rather than a modern man. Is this a true portrayal of a modern retired English soldier?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_127037'><a id="like_count_community_question_127037" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/127037?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">8 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F6643090-major-pettigrew-s-last-stand">like</a></span>

