<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/36072849-sherri-robinson"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1413650646i/36072849._UX100_CR0,5,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/36072849-sherri-robinson">Sherri Robinson</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I have found that many career military men are very dependent on their wives to negotiate life as a civilian. Their bafflement of navigating daily lif<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I have found that many career military men are very dependent on their wives to negotiate life as a civilian. Their bafflement of navigating daily life can make them appear older when out of the routine. I thing small towns are universal because the people stay in them generation after generation. Staying means holding to the past and not even thinking there are different ways of doing things and being uncomfortable with changes. We've done it this way for decades, what is wrong with that?<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
